critique: This executive order pertains to the temporary import of culturally significant objects. It delegates presidential authority to the Secretary of State to make determinations about the cultural significance and national interest of such objects. It doesn't directly address ideological issues, immigration, or civil liberties. It has a slight impact on executive power by delegating authority, and a very slight impact on federalism by involving the federal government in cultural matters. It has no impact on economic regulation or social inclusion.
